Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content:
The bestk stuff will take thousands of notarizatons to even out. As its randomly chosen. 
Also because f updates, not all nodes are in recvmask for long enough to have any meaningful result.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: Might take a few days even a week to know if it works as intended. One Thing I cna say for sure is its 100x better than it was.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: We have bearly minsigs nodes online, so mostl of the time the same nodes wil be chosen, because they are the only ones that comitted to the recvmask.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content:
Maybe I need to add some logging on the iguana side, to log which nodes are in the recvmask each round. 
That will give us something to filters out nodes with lower counts that were not actually  up the entire time. 
The bestk rotates via the block height, but it does not notarize every 5th block,  so it takes many days to average out to the same numbers.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: @SHossain  please read the document pinned in #priv-notarynode , it explains how the bestks and best mask is chosen in great detail with examples, if it is not doing what this document describes, then it is a bug, and I still have not fixed it.
